40-EXP-Classic-MTB-800x448.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/DT-Swiss-240-Oil-Slick-Limited-edition-mountain-bike-hubs_240-EXP-Classic-MTB-120x67.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/DT-Swiss-240-Oil-Slick-Limited-edition-mountain-bike-hubs_240-EXP-Classic-MTB-768x430.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/DT-Swiss-240-Oil-Slick-Limited-edition-mountain-bike-hubs_240-EXP-Classic-MTB-696x390.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/DT-Swiss-240-Oil-Slick-Limited-edition-mountain-bike-hubs_240-EXP-Classic-MTB-1068x598.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/DT-Swiss-240-Oil-Slick-Limited-edition-mountain-bike-hubs_240-EXP-Classic-MTB-750x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 750w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-252394\">c. DT Swiss</figcaption></figure><p>It’s not an entirely new finish for DT Swiss hubs, and to be fair to DT, their first oil slick hubs pre-date at least another twenty-five “<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=%22oil+slick%22\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">oil slick</a>” components we’ve seen in the last year. But the DT Swiss shininess has never been easy to get ahold of.</p><p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020-Canyon-Lux-CF-SLX-9-DT-Swiss-232-Race-Limited-edition_special-Olympic-race-edition-carbon-full-suspension-XC-mountain-bike_complete.jpg\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020-Canyon-Lux-CF-SLX-9-DT-Swiss-232-Race-Limited-edition_special-Olympic-race-edition-carbon-full-suspension-XC-mountain-bike_complete.jpg\"></p><p>Last winter we saw the ultra-limited edition <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/23/limited-edition-canyon-lux-cf-slx-9-0-dt-swiss-race-is-first-with-dt-232-suspension/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Canyon Lux CF SLX 9.0 DT LTD</a>, which debuted DT Swiss’ new 232 cross-country suspension, also get a set of wheels built up with oil slick hubs.</p><p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020-Canyon-Lux-CF-SLX-9-DT-Swiss-232-Race-Limited-edition_special-Olympic-race-edition-carbon-full-suspension-XC-mountain-bike_DT-XMC1200-Spline-30-oil-slick-wheels.jpg\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020-Canyon-Lux-CF-SLX-9-DT-Swiss-232-Race-Limited-edition_special-Olympic-race-edition-carbon-full-suspension-XC-mountain-bike_DT-XMC1200-Spline-30-oil-slick-wheels.jpg\"></p><p>The straight-pull hubs in those XRC1200 carbon wheels were an OEM-exclusive finish (as were the two matching spokes), and the only way to get them was to buy one of the 32 complete bikes.</p><p>Starting last summer, a rare set of those Centerlock, straight-pull hubs would occasionally pop up. I saw a set with Belgian builder <a href=\"https://www.stealthwheels.be/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Stealth Wheels</a> and another in German custom builder <a href=\"https://www.light-wolf.de/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Light-Wolf</a>‘s display cabinet, having already been claimed by a customer.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/DT-Swiss-240-Oil-Slick-Limited-edition-mountain-bike-hubs_240-EXP-Classic-MTB-rainbow-hubset.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/DT-Swiss-240-Oil-Slick-Limited-ed